This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on camera localization, which is a common problem in computer vision. It also proposes a new approach to robust optimization, which is a key component in many computer vision applications. 

The paper also touches on reinforcement learning, which suggests that it could belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. 

The use of deep learning pipelines and the focus on optimization suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as camera localization is important in computer graphics applications such as augmented reality and virtual reality.
